VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \b(getenv|setenv|putenv|clearenv)\s*\(
WHEN EXPR MISSING:validate|sanitize|allowlist|whitelist|check\s*\(|strlen|strnlen
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects the usage of functions that access or modify the process environment.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Unsafe Use of Process Environment Variables.
